|YKOCombat in DarkWind runs on heartbeats. Every round, each of your
attacks -- wielded weapons, or fists and natural attacks without them --
produces one or more swings, and every swing rolls on its own to crit,
hit, be dodged, be absorbed, and finally deal damage.

Starting a fight: |YKBkill <target>|YKO opens combat, and most offensive
guild abilities do the same. Judge a target's experience first with
|YKBassess <target>|YKO. Attacking other players requires Player
Killing registration; read |CKBhelp pk|YKO first. See |CKBhelp kill|YKO.

Landing hits: how often you swing depends on your weapon's size and
speed and on your strength and dexterity, with diminishing returns at
high stat values. Whether a swing lands pits
your level, intelligence, and dexterity, plus your weapon's accuracy,
against the defender's dodge. Roughly one swing in twenty is a critical
hit for multiplied damage. Weapon training sharpens all of this -- see
|CKBhelp specialization|YKO.

Dealing damage: damage comes from your damage stat and your weapon's
damage class. Heavier and two-handed weapons hit harder but swing
slower and less accurately. Damage carries types (slashing, fire, and
so on) that are checked against the defender's resistances.

Defending: dodge avoids swings outright. Armour's absorb class applies
reliable flat and percentage reduction to physical weapon damage, and
can also absorb a landed blow down to nothing. Armour-piercing attacks
halve that reliable reduction. Resistances and magical shields shave
typed damage away. Spells and potions layer on more protection -- see
|CKBhelp buffs|YKO and |CKBhelp shields|YKO. Check your armor class and
weapon class anytime with |YKBsc|YKO.

Running away: you can flee any fight by simply leaving the room, though
a pursuer who catches you gets a free swing. |YKBwimpy <percent>|YKO
makes your legs flee automatically at low health; see |CKBhelp wimpy|YKO.

Dying: death costs 10% of your experience on hand (nothing at level 5
or under) and your corpse stays safely with you. See |CKBhelp death|YKO.

Fighting together: |YKBassist <player>|YKO joins a friend's fight, and
parties split the work and the reward; see |CKBhelp party|YKO. Trim
combat spam with |YKBcombatbrief|YKO.|XX0

